{
  "stem": "11290.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That fear was so great that I even, when I once was free in America, I still remember that we used to talk always in hushed voices when anything slightly political came up.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That took a long time to assimilate to a free society.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at that time I was still hoping that they will soon come.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I, I-- we were working on their emigration, and I was telling them that it wasn't so terrible to come to America, that they would probably be glad to be here.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were willing, and, and, and in fact, they worked on-- began to work on it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And only after the Kristallnacht, it was made impossible because my father was then taken from his home.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And also he was a sick, old man, really.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He was not that old, but he wasn't well.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was taken to Dachau with every Jewish man from Munich or from any German city-- not all to Dachau, but they were all taken to concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were treated horribly there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a cold November night.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had to shed all their clothes and stand shivering for hours naked in the-- in the open air.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My uncle, my father's brother, who was with him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was in the same-- in the same group, arrested together with my father.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They only lived a few blocks away from each other, and he was in the same group.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the doctors had no-- there was a couple of Jewish doctors in the concentration camp also together with my father.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When my father started to get sick, they couldn't take care of him because they had no way of, of pasteurizing anything, or, or any instruments or anything with them.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
